{"data":{"page":{"coverImage":{"title":"Black and white wolf pack","alt":"Photo by Tom Pottiger on Unsplash","fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.504201680672269,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=1920&q=50","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=480&h=319&q=50 480w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=960&h=638&q=50 960w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=1920&h=1276&q=50 1920w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=2880&h=1915&q=50 2880w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=3840&h=2553&q=50 3840w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1amyHoJENrI41Oezx2MPoX/9edb460c7fbbd2572de1ee651e452e6a/tom-pottiger-557010-unsplash.jpg?w=5012&h=3332&q=50 5012w","sizes":"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"}},"content":{"json":{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Quick recap…so far in the ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"id":"c7eZIW7N3VRvPJEHqSIxSfw","type":"Link","linkType":"Entry"}}},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Framework Journey","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"entry-hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" series, you’ve mapped out a life blueprint and parted the Red Sea of stress that was preventing you from ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"id":"c19BQk7laykTjDRGV5IJ9Ug","type":"Link","linkType":"Entry"}}},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"escaping your 9–5 job","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"entry-hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":".","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Whether you decided to go part-time, start a side hustle, or full-out quit, this week is going to be fun. We’re going to start building our freedom business by zeroing in on the types of people we can connect with.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Part 1: Defining Your Tribe","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"This is often referred to as finding your “audience,” but I like the word “tribe” because it’s more dramatic. After all, we’re not just looking for people to listen to us or buy our stuff. We want to create a community that grows over time — a band of like-minded warriors (lovers, etc) who will rally around a meaningful idea.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"So, how do we do that?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"It helps to understand that there are two basic types of followers:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"People who want to ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"support ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"you","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"People who want to ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"become","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" you","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"For example, a musician has fans who will pay to see a live show (supporting), while a fitness coach has students who will pay for a private session so they can get in shape (becoming).","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"I bet you’ve taken on these roles at different times in your life. And the easiest way to figure out who ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"your","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" followers might be is to step into the shoes of a younger self — what problems were you dealing with at the time? How did you solve them?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Let’s do a little exploring…","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Reverse-engineering your followers","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"First, in a new page (Google Docs, Notion, your notebook, etc), create a table with four columns: Archetype, Follower, Motivation, Desired State. In column one, copy over your top five archetypes from the ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"id":"c7eZIW7N3VRvPJEHqSIxSfw","type":"Link","linkType":"Entry"}}},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"life blueprint","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"entry-hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" you created in week one.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"In column two, think about the person you were BEFORE you solved a really frustrating problem related to that archetype. For example: when I feel uncreative, I become a Consumer. I start watching or reading interesting content (Motivation), so I can be inspired, creatively (Desired State).","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Go ahead and fill out the rest of your table. You can use mine as a reference.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"jbawaa5001ko"}},"id":"c1cOF9UQFhR8heoBBfh6kYH","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-04-28T21:29:54.674Z","updatedAt":"2019-04-28T21:29:54.674Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1},"fields":{"title":{"en-US":"Tribe Archetypes chart"},"file":{"en-US":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1cOF9UQFhR8heoBBfh6kYH/c08f568f531480052f4f21d649e5a953/tribe-archetypes.png","details":{"size":61303,"image":{"width":932,"height":451}},"fileName":"tribe-archetypes.png","contentType":"image/png"}}}}},"content":[],"nodeType":"embedded-asset-block"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Done? Nice. Even though you don’t know WHAT kind of business you’re going to create or WHO will be in your tribe, you now have a general sense of WHY someone might follow you. Next, let’s back that up by figuring out how you can help your followers grow.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Part 2: Being a Leader Worth Following","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"It goes without saying that to be a good leader you need to have some valuable skills or qualities. You also need to decide which ones you can build a tribe around. To do that, let’s create a table with the following columns:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Pursuit:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" the skill or quality, itself","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Passion:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" enjoyment, motivation to improve","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Ability:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" your natural talent","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Experience:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" having done something many times","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"value":"Knowledge:","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" facts and abstract concepts","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Drop in as many pursuits as you can think of, then (for each) check off Passion, Ability, Experience, and Knowledge if they apply. In the next couple sections, we’re going to use these resources to build a killer niche. ","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"These are a few of mine…","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"jbawaa5001ko"}},"id":"c1uMynVBJZ56YzcrJrgj444","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-04-28T21:28:33.701Z","updatedAt":"2019-04-28T21:28:41.510Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2},"fields":{"title":{"en-US":"Leadership Ingredients chart"},"file":{"en-US":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1uMynVBJZ56YzcrJrgj444/2b92e4af20d4e1a4c7f92d5f7c3897fa/padded-image.jpg","details":{"size":106614,"image":{"width":932,"height":501}},"fileName":"padded-image.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg"}}}}},"content":[],"nodeType":"embedded-asset-block"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Perfect vs Extraordinary","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If you want to build a following, you need be unique — you need to carve out a slice of the universe that no one else owns. There are only two ways to do this:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Be the best at something that already exists (almost impossible)","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Be really good at something new (difficult, but doable)","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"ordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.google.com/search?q=usain+bolt&oq=usain+bolt"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Usain Bolt","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" is an example of the first strategy. There are thousands of runners who are ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"almost","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" as fast as he is, but no matter how close they come, people aren’t going to remember the second-best runner in the world (let alone the third or forth, etc).","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Another word for chasing perfection is “","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.google.com/search?q=asymptote"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"asymptote","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":",” which means a line a that continually approaches a curve, but does not meet it at any finite distance. Seth Godin riffs on this in ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://amzn.to/2Szzj5g"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"Linchpin","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":": “[People who] earn dramatic success always do it in markets where asymptotes don’t exist, or where they can be shattered.”","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Niche Recipes","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"General topics like “health and fitness” are really hard to break into. There are a million businesses already serving those audiences (and only a tiny fraction are really successful). The way to get around this is by bringing together two or more generic ideas to create something remarkable.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Here’s my favorite example: ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zaLOoVjFc08"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Marc Ribellet","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" is a YouTuber who makes loop-based songs with goofy voiceovers and interludes.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"jbawaa5001ko"}},"id":"gvQaMlcF3gy6T8Pm4Vy8l","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-04-28T21:25:34.379Z","updatedAt":"2019-04-28T21:25:34.379Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"video"}}},"fields":{"title":{"en-US":"Marc Rebillet: Sorry to Bother You"},"url":{"en-US":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_hwdOCZ340"}}}},"content":[],"nodeType":"embedded-entry-block"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"The dude’s hilarious, musically talented, and wildly imaginative, but he isn’t the best in the world at any of those things. However…because he combined them into an entirely new niche, he was able to go from ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4pBZsmvavMM"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"nothing","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" to almost ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=E_hwdOCZ340&t=4708s"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"200k subscribers","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" in just two years.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"How did he do it? No clue. But I can make an educated guess:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"People who watch Marc’s videos probably want to be entertained, but more than that, they want to be energized, creatively. It’s hard to find content like that on YouTube — most videos are designed to distract you, not motivate you. Marc solved the problem by combining three of his skills (music, comedy, and improvisation) into a killer niche. To summarize…","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Desired State","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Roadblock","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Combo Solution","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Go ahead and create 2–3 niche recipes of your own. What’d you come up with? Tweet your best to me ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://www.twitter.com/fthelines"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"@fthelines","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":". Here’s where I landed:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"Creative people want the freedom to explore, but their lack of focus traps them in bad situations and prevents them from becoming financially independent. I’m going to solve that problem by teaching business skills to creatives through writing, conversations with unconventional entrepreneurs, and hands-on experience (learning as I go).","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Part 3: Finding the Touch Points","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Now that we know what our potential tribe members might be feeling and we’ve carved out a unique solution that could be helpful, let’s figure out where we can actually find them.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"To do that, we need to get a little more specific on ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"value":"who","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" these people are. Pick your strongest problem/solution scenario and think about what types of people might be struggling with that issue. Jot down any characteristics that come to mind. For example, I wrote:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Artists, designers, developers, writers","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Creative freelancers","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Creatives working at agencies","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Freewheeling, not conservative","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Disorganized, scatter-brained","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Not business-savvy","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Dislikes the status quo","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"No-bullshit, tell it like it is","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"21–35 years old","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Philosophical/deep","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Passionate, idealistic","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"More introverted than extraverted","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"list-item"}],"nodeType":"unordered-list"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Scanning for human lifeforms…","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"The next question to ask is, “Where do these kinds of people hang out?” You will probably have a lot in common with your future tribe members, so you can also ask, “Where did I spend a lot of time when I was __ years old?” Or “…when I was struggling with X,” etc.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Literally imagine their day from the time they wake up to the time they go to sleep. (We’re going to creep a bit in the name of research.) What podcasts do they listen to? What social media apps are they on? Do they go to meetups? Are they buying tickets to tech conferences? Which hashtags or topics are they following?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"For my tribe, Reddit and Twitter come to mind first, because that’s where a lot of freelancers go to complain about #clientsfromhell and get advice, etc. I think Medium probably makes sense, as well, because a lot of people are sharing/searching for stories about personal struggles and what they learned. Design conferences or meetups could be helpful — it’s sometimes easier (and quicker) to just meet in person.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Making contact","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-3"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Now, to wrap up, let me say that your goal right now is not to start pitching people on a business that doesn’t even exist. The whole point of this article is to help you start generating some authentic connections, so you can get a clearer understanding of why you should create a tribe in the first place:","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"What do people really want? Why are they struggling? What specific roadblocks are stopping them? What solutions have already tried, and why didn’t they work? What has worked? All this stuff is pure gold, and you’ll find that most people are more than willing to tell you about their problems.","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Next Steps: Creating a Business Plan","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Alright, troopers. Good work. We’ve laid the groundwork for a killer target audience, and now it’s time for you to get out there and start connecting. Your assignment for this week is to talk with one person each day. If you can handle more, great, but by next week I want you to have connected with at least seven people. Let’s do this!","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Next week, we’re gunna get all businessy by creating a solid plan for our new venture. So look out for that email. The subject line is “FTL / Week 4: Creating a Business Plan.” If you’re not already subscribed to the Framework Journey series, you can ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://pages.convertkit.com/b4bc0f01ed/3f59dd8f63"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"click here","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":".","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"},{"data":{"target":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"jbawaa5001ko"}},"id":"c1tctYJd9w9WwKr3CrFQqRJ","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-04-28T21:27:07.508Z","updatedAt":"2019-04-28T21:27:07.508Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1},"fields":{"title":{"en-US":"ET Finger"},"file":{"en-US":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/1tctYJd9w9WwKr3CrFQqRJ/7e2db192e6848a299c67e6480f7c088e/et-finger.gif","details":{"size":1627596,"image":{"width":400,"height":203}},"fileName":"et-finger.gif","contentType":"image/gif"}}}}},"content":[],"nodeType":"embedded-asset-block"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"Hungry for more?","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"heading-2"},{"data":{},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"If you’re ready to start making some serious changes and pursue the life you want, let’s connect. You can get weekly advice by ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://pages.convertkit.com/b4bc0f01ed/3f59dd8f63"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"clicking here","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":" or get in touch with me on Twitter ","nodeType":"text"},{"data":{"uri":"https://twitter.com/fthelines"},"content":[{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":"@fthelines","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"hyperlink"},{"data":{},"marks":[],"value":".","nodeType":"text"}],"nodeType":"paragraph"}],"nodeType":"document"}},"__typename":"ContentfulArticle","id":"ce034939-981d-5cff-a3bf-fc06d7e11bef","slug":"finding-your-tribe-killer-target-audience","title":"Finding Your Tribe: How to Define a Killer Target Audience","updatedAt":"2019-04-28T22:56:47.076Z","updatedAtString":"Apr 28, 2019 at 10:56pm","summary":{"text":"Whether you want to be a musician or design expert you won't get far without an audience. This week, we're learning how to become a leader worth following."},"fullPublishDate":"April 1, 2019","publishDate":"2019-04-29T16:52","author":{"name":"Andrew Folts","avatar":{"title":"Andrew Folts profile photo","alt":"","fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/2zp1feJo07IiG6YwZXudNr/ecc0f0eaf4e5952ddef7f0a3bb706569/smiling-lumberjack-1.jpg?w=800&q=50","srcSet":"//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/2zp1feJo07IiG6YwZXudNr/ecc0f0eaf4e5952ddef7f0a3bb706569/smiling-lumberjack-1.jpg?w=200&h=200&q=50 200w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/2zp1feJo07IiG6YwZXudNr/ecc0f0eaf4e5952ddef7f0a3bb706569/smiling-lumberjack-1.jpg?w=400&h=400&q=50 400w,\n//images.ctfassets.net/jbawaa5001ko/2zp1feJo07IiG6YwZXudNr/ecc0f0eaf4e5952ddef7f0a3bb706569/smiling-lumberjack-1.jpg?w=628&h=628&q=50 628w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"relatedArticles":null}},"pageContext":{"slug":"finding-your-tribe-killer-target-audience"}}